<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="238" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1348,1591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1348,1374]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">
<typeStatus box="[151,210,1348,1374]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">Type</typeStatus>
data:
</emphasis>
This 
<taxonomicName box="[350,481,1348,1375]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" rank="variety" variety="was">variety was</taxonomicName>
described based on a single male specimen collected by the German scientist Curt Schrottky (1874–1937) in Jundiaí, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[693,765,1384,1410]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Schrottky was one of the first European entomologist who resided in South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmussen, C. &amp; Garcete-Barrett, B. F. &amp; Goncalves, R. B." box="[452,713,1420,1447]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref23073" refString="Rasmussen, C., Garcete-Barrett, B. F. &amp; Goncalves, R. B. (2009) Curt Schrottky (1874 - 1937): South American entomology at the beginning of the 20 th century (Hymenoptera, Lepidoptera, Diptera). Zootaxa, 2282 (1), 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2282.1.1" type="journal article" year="2009">
Rasmussen 
<emphasis box="[588,638,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). Once in 
<collectingCountry box="[829,900,1420,1446]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, he settled in 
<collectingRegion box="[1056,1228,1420,1447]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmussen, C. &amp; Garcete-Barrett, B. F. &amp; Goncalves, R. B." pageId="7" pageNumber="238" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref23073" refString="Rasmussen, C., Garcete-Barrett, B. F. &amp; Goncalves, R. B. (2009) Curt Schrottky (1874 - 1937): South American entomology at the beginning of the 20 th century (Hymenoptera, Lepidoptera, Diptera). Zootaxa, 2282 (1), 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2282.1.1" type="journal article" year="2009">
Rasmussen 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). He started collecting insects in the city of Jundiaí, where the specimen studied by Friese was caught.
</paragraph>
